23/01/2007
MOSCOW, Russia -- Republika Srpska (RS) Prime Minister Milorad Dodik arrived on Monday (January 22nd) in Moscow for talks on bilateral economic co-operation. 
According to an official statement in Banja Luka, the visit is aimed at resolving final details of a protocol signed last year between the RS cabinet and Russia's Zarubezhneft. 
It envisions the purchase of the RS state-run oil refinery Bosanski Brod, the motor and industrial oil manufacturer Modrica and the fuel retailer Petrol. 
(Nezavisne novine - 23/01/07; RTRS, RS government website, PBS BiH, Itar-Tass - 22/01/07)
